After YEARS of our good friends telling us we "just have to try it"...we did get there.  To be fair, we did take out (COVID 19 restrictions and convenience drove our desire to take out).  So...the shoyu pork was SUPER TENDER, and flavorful...UNFORTUNATELY, the shoyu pork was topmost plate and 1 of 4 plates that we ordered, and that was packed in one bag.  The 20 minute drive home led to the shoyu pork plate spilling over as the plate at the bottom collapsed under the weight of the 3 other plates above it.  SO, for us, everything under that shoyu pork (again, it was pretty good) had a nice enhanced flavor of the shoyu pork sauce.  IF you order take out from them...ask them to pack no more than 2 per bag (or whatever depending on what your order is), just so you avoid what happened to us.  Pictured is the bottom most plate, and the amount of shoyu pork sauce that was in the bottom of the bag after unpacking.

Holy cow! I have been in this state for three days and I can already see myself eating here again and again.  The food was excellent, (even though it had to be delivered).  When it arrived it was well packaged, food looked great in the travel tray, I can only imagine how much better it will look on the plate. Everything we asked for arrived, so no annoying call back necessary, therefore I am taking the time to acknowledge this business instead. We had the fried chicken, excellent! The Korean bbq beef, fantastic! The egg whites with veggies, scrumptious! And the pineapple cream pancakes, pure heaven!!! lol.  Thank you! See you soon!!
The miso butterfish and potato salad were delicious. My family owned a restaurant for 35 years and I'm very critical of other restaurants,  but Pioneer Saloon is outstanding.

Food is alright but the customer service is pretty junk.  The manager or owner... who ever is looking over the business seems very picky on who he decides to help and when pouring water into jugs is more important than customer interaction. You may wait a few minutes to be helped, or a few hours to be helped... If any sane person would stay that long without dying of hunger first.  I suggest going to the main location near Diamond Head instead.
gets pretty crowded during lunch, but overall good atmosphere & food. indoor & outdoor seating available. don't forget to validate your parking before you leave!

I love Pioneer Saloon!! The food is so good!! So many choices and I have yet to be disappointed. My faves are Baby Tako, anything Salmon, anything Scallops....and I always get Shiso Rice!!  Things can get chaotic when they are busy so patience is a must. Or go on off times! Parking is easy and validated at SALT. Check it out! I love it!

Worst service I've ever had at any restaurant. We were seated. We ordered. We never got any food. After  an hour I asked what was up, and they just couldn't find my order and the server only vaguely remembered why we were sitting there. Original pioneer is good. This pioneer sucks.
Food was great at a reasonable price. Parking can be tricky and they ran out of a lot of food by the tail end of a normal dinner time, just shy of 8pm.
The Ahi furikaki katsu is the best yet (take that Ohana in Seattle!). And the staff is always friendly. I go into foodie depression if I skip a week.

If you like to get your restaurant meals the way you order them, I wouldn't eat here.   I only like a particular dish served the way they do it in Japan, so before ordering from Pioneer's menu, I asked if it was served with that condiment  and was told it was.  When the meal arrived, the condiment I had asked about was missing.  The server told me he'd bring it.  I waited.  Slowly ate all the salad.  Slowly ate all the rice.  By now, my entree is cold, unpalatable and not anything I'd want to eat even if he'd brought the condiment.   They weren't even that busy.

Love the original pioneer. This one is not as good. Maybe they will figure it out, but it is just not right currently. Garlic thin slice pork bowl the eggs are supposed to be runny. Even says sunny side up on menu. They come fried hard. I ask the staff and they just shrug. My wife orders the pork cutlet bowl which is supposed to come with sides. They bring it with none. We ask the wait staff and one says it doesnt and the other says it does. So she gets no sides. Person next to us orders same thing and gets sides. It makes no sense. They do not offer to fix either my overcooked eggs or her lack of sides. They do not even know how their own menu is supposed to be. It is sad to see the original pioneer's reputation pulled down by this place.
Sauce and flavor was good but thin sliced beef had more fat than beef. Too expensive for what you get
Meh food and took forever!  There's no reason to wait over 40 minutes for run of the mill local food.
Great food options and nice outdoor seating area!

Pioneer is one of my favorite eating spots on Oahu. Having one open in my hood is a major bonus. The food is similar to what's at Diamond Head location but they plan to make Kakaako specific menu soon.  If you come to Kakaako grab a bite at Pioneer and Take some trendy pics around the way with plenty of Pow Wow Murals.

Pioneer has been long coming to SALT, add the large amount of people who frequent this area and the specific spectrum this place fill, you bet the first week they are open they will have a large welcome, with it's weight of needs.  Food is great as expected. Interior is nice and pleasant, and staff- even when under the pressure of opening in demand- was very friendly and in full communication.  Some parts of the bar along the wall has outlets, a good place to do some small work or recharging while you munch away.
